# Terraform Core (Implementation)

- **Small diffs:** Prefer incremental changes. One logical change per edit session; avoid bundling unrelated fixes.
- **No scope creep:** Implement only what the task or design log specifies. Do not add new resources or modules unless explicitly asked.
- **Providers:** Do not add new providers or change provider versions unless the user or design log explicitly requests them.
- **Verification:** After edits, run from the relevant module or repo root:
  - `terraform fmt -recursive`
  - `terraform validate`
  - Optionally `terraform plan` (no apply in automation unless intended). Fix any failures before considering the task done.
- **State and sensitive data:** Do not hardcode secrets; use variables or external secret management. Be aware of state implications (e.g. destroy/recreate) when changing identifiers.
